Author: sarahsweetchilli
Content: Is there any platform for non-techy users to contribute to datasets or aggregate / annotate data?

Author: sarahsweetchilli
Content:
*Example:* I'm a non-techy person with a lot of pictures on my phone and I want to make money from this data. 

*Another Example* I am a person with spare time, who isn't familiar with AI or machine learning, and I want to make side money from data annotation or data generation (these are repetitive and simple jobs once the fundamentals are laid down)

Author: sarahsweetchilli
Content: Right now the people selling datasets are people who have already aggregated and annotated data. To my knowledge most of these people are business managers, crypto nerds or AI experts. Nothing wrong with this, it's just a niche audience.

Author: sarahsweetchilli
Content: Ocean could appeal to the entire world, rather than just experts, if we make data annotation accessible & profitable for the average person. If we build dApps that allow normal people to upload + annotate data in their spare time and make a bit of cash whilst doing it--say, they can draw bounding boxes around pictures from their phones--we would increase Ocean's fundamental value whilst creating casual jobs.

Author: sarahsweetchilli
Content: Forgive me if anything I've said is wrong or ignorant, I'm still learning. I have had this idea for a while and I think you guys would like to hear it. If such a dApp is already being developed, let me know. If not, I would like to start on something

Author: sarahsweetchilli
Content: Yes ^ And these tasks are mostly performed by AI experts. Their labor is better used on building models and setting up programs, not on this repetition

Author: sarahsweetchilli
Content: Last night I told my programmer mate about Ocean for the first time, he asked whats the difference between the Ocean marketplace and a marketplace where you can trade regular USD for data

Author: sarahsweetchilli
Content: How would you guys answer this question?

Author: sarahsweetchilli
robinlehmann
Content:
If you calculate in the costs for swapping USDT -> ETH or BNT (if you use Bancor) -> OCEAN via DEXes or the cost for USDT -> OCEAN on Binance you get a price that would be equivalent to USD.
But in general this could be seen as a temporal problem as there will probably soon be options to just pay with USD. Just a matter of time and adoption.
For DataUnion.app we will (at some point) have offramps to BTC, USDT, USD, EUR etc. and probably also onramps as this basically enables more consumers and contributors to consume/participate in the dataset.

Author: robinlehmann
Content: You could also hedge against this by creating longs and shorts on OCEAN to reduce the risk. This is like with stocks to secure against volatility.

Author: nmjchbu
Content:
Hey thanks so much! Glad to be here 😄 Yes Nima and Shreyas if you know him.  

NEAR has a similar sort of ambassador program, except it's called a "guild" system. Guilds can be literally anything from Technical Analysis guilds or Solidity Developers, anything and everything crypto related. So my initial thought was that since theres this guild system that can produce such specialized and "peer reviewed"  data, which would easily be monetizable on the OCEAN marketplace. So I'm sure there's already some guilds who intend to do exactly this,  so I thought maybe creating some sort of incentive program/strategic partnership might be worthwhile,  which would only grow both ecosystems positively.

Author: nmjchbu
Content: Once again, was just the first thought to pop in my head, entirely open to explore otherwise 🙂

Author: robinlehmann
Content:
Ocean Protocol is not available on the NEAR blockchain, so that would be the first thing that would be a collaboration - make it possible to use Ocean Protocol on NEAR. NEAR promises to deliver scalability and low cost transactions on its blockchain but also a compatibility with Ethereum via their Rainbow bridge.
It would be a great collaboration to make it possible that the project is usable on both blockchains.
After that the data collection can be done and offered on both blockchains at the same time.
That would be my initial thoughts about NEAR and Ocean synergies.

Author: robinlehmann
Content:
A few questions to help us help you - how long will the video be?
I saw your previous video and from what I understand the platform you are using to create them is providing you with images/objects and effects to create the video, right?

What is Ocean?
This is covered well by the Mission statement of Ocean here:
https://oceanprotocol.com/about

From my point of view the core components of Ocean Protocol have been created in the past - namely: marketplaces, compute-to-data and datatokens as well as the beginning of the OceanDAO. This can all be used to enhance Data Science.
That are the achievements.

What is still outstanding from the technical point of view is the integration of compute-to-data into the marketplace itself.
The only thing that is publicly know about it can be found in the roadmap of Ocean: https://oceanprotocol.com/roadmap
Quote:

In Ocean Market: buy & sell private data while preserving privacy
Mitigates risk of buyer-supplied malicious algorithms, via whitelisted algorithms or workflow for publisher to vet algorithms

To me this means that data can be sold without having to leave the storage of the data provider. Also that this data cannot be copied by the buyer.
But that the compute done by the algorithms are also covered by the data provider via their hardware. And that the data buyer will pay for this compute.

Author: .scottm3
Content:
Hi everyone, Scott here. I’m excited to join and discover how I can best use my skillset to help build on Ocean’s vision. I work in Product Development/Management and recently negotiated and implemented a $6.5m USD development contract with over 40 developers and designers. 

I’m eager to build products and am open to submitting a proposal for review but don’t yet have a strong use case. I’ve been speaking with @Mark about the positioning/business strategy with Ocean and keen to explore this topic in more detail. We collaborated on a question for the community below:

Author: .scottm3
Content:
The objective of this question is to get a clear understanding of the unique value proposition of Ocean so that we can better serve, and strategically implement Ocean Protocol’s vision in the market. 

As we understand, the Ocean protocol is ultimately a 2 sided marketplace connecting buyers and sellers of data. One could have a popular dataset on an Ocean Market which generates $500,000 in revenue and another person may have 500 datasets on Ocean Market generating $0 in revenue based on the demand for their data assets. 

It’s possible (but unlikely) that I am going to receive a lot of money for sharing my personal location data. Even in the best case scenario I may generate a few $100 dollars which some may find attractive but most will encounter too much friction/hesitation towards opening up and sharing their personal data for some relatively small sum of money. (This may not be the case in all situations/countries as a few hundred dollars will be a lot of money but in those cases the buying power of that consumer base would be lower and therefore the incentive for businesses to leverage that data would be lower also).

Author: .scottm3
Content:
Therefore, the higher value datasets for Ocean are likely those held in big privately held databases or brokered in other partnering models like: www.datarade.ai which could:
    1.    Benefit from being used in machine learning algorithms, AI etc to create value (i.e. there is demand for the data). 
    2.    Be sold to the market without the company receiving a significant backlash from existing customers/business partners/shareholders i.e. the benefits of enabling access to the data (revenues generated) outweigh the costs of providing secure access to the data for the market to consume. One could imagine a backlash against a local retailer if customers discovered that all of a sudden their shopping data was being sold by the retailer for profit.
This is where we start to get a little stuck… If there is huge revenue potential sitting behind closed doors (in privately held databases), then why wouldn’t a more traditional private company have come along and given the owners of these datasets the ability to compute against the datasets privately? Is this the secret sauce that’s only enabled through Ocean Protocol?

If not, then is it the open, networked and decentralised nature of the Ocean Protocol? Under this assumption we are assuming that an open, networked and decentralised org structure is the superior org structure for executing on this opportunity. 

It would be great to better understand this topic so that we can more accurately convey the USP to the market. Knowing the answer to this should also help indicate where to start looking for new business opportunities with Ocean.

Author: robinlehmann
Content:
The secret sauce part with compute to data is one important factor but the other factor that makes Ocean standout is the pricing mechanism of the assets.
This expands Ocean from being a two sided market to much more. The stakers become a part of the market as well. They curate, price and validate datasets but also benefit from that.

The combination of these features makes Ocean a 🦄.

I am very open to have sessions with you and @Mark to discuss this further and create an overview and analysis paper.

Author: Frederic#8800
Content:
(Damn, Robin was already here while I was typing 😄 As always 🚀 👏🏼 )

Hi Scott! These are super valuable thoughts. Thanks for sharing!
The answer includes my personal perspective, there is potentially a lot more, but this is what is important in my opinion:

With compute-to-data you can sell data access without having the problems you mentioned. If set up correctly, there is no “backslash” from customers/business partners/shareholders because the data is never moved, data consumers never see the data itself.

Still, you (and any buyer) can generate insights on private data in a fully compliant way. This includes machine learning, business analytics, or other forms of data aggregation. It’s not about the data owner who can compute here. It’s about any potential buyer. And because Ocean is permissionless, this could be anyone.

As you say, this is a risk/reward trade-off. And the more sensitive the data, the more security you need to balance the risk. 

Data monetization makes sense for traditional companies in many cases, even when companies compete. MOBI is an example where traditional automakers can potentially share datasets for autonomous driving (without giving away the data) to compete with Tesla. In other cases, data can be a “byproduct” of a companies core business. In this case, it’s only a cost-center and they could start monetizing it. Compared to what is on the market right now, C2D is more about huge and valuable datasets. There are many similar examples we could think of.

“Turn your data storage into a profit center” (while keeping ownership and full control and being compliant) is one of the opportunities here.

Author: .scottm3
Content:
Hi @Robin | DataUnion , @Frederic and @kaimeinke thank you for your thoughts. 
The pricing mechanism is definitely an interesting feature and one where the incentives that exist would probably be harder to replicate in a private model (in my head I keep comparing this to a private venture, not to discredit the Ocean project but to instead uncover the unique benefits of OP). Staking tokens on datasets encourages market participants to curate good data and send a signal to the market that ‘this is good data’ which is great. 

Open and permissionless access to data for C2D applications to run on is also another great benefit. Assuming this means that some people (with good intentions!) are accessing datasets they couldn’t otherwise access through other third party providers already. 

Data unions and shared data initiatives (like scanning bills and monetising as a group) is also a unique and interesting concept. In theory I could probably start something like that today (as a private venture) but be subject to a number of local laws and regulations (friction) and so doing something like this on OP where the incentives are closer to the consumer than they maybe are in a private model could be a unique benefit.

Author: .scottm3
Content:
Thinking these scenarios through is starting to lead me down the path of… maybe the networked, permissionless and incentive based model is a fundamentally superior model for mass scale than a private model. i.e. a private company can only hire so quickly, expand into new markets so quickly and jump on new trends so quickly. In other words it can only spread its incentives so thinly before it runs out. 

OP (and other decentralised projects for that matter) are more organic and take on a life of their own. As they are open and permissionless, anyone can jump on board, have a go, at no cost to the overarching entity (OP) i.e, not many people are spending their spare time thinking up new ways for Jeff Bezos to grow his empire - he has to employ people to do that for him. 

Therefore, those that jump on board and build things the market wants are rewarded and those that don’t, simply try again or fade away. The equivalent would be trying to convince a bunch of investors to invest in a private company where we will pay anyone who walks in through the door to do stuff and some will succeed and others will fail but we don’t really know what’s going to happen. 😆 

I feel like I’ve either gone on a complete tangent or am touching on something fundamentally important?

Author: robinlehmann
Content:
Bruce said at some point that AMMs and accompanying DEXs are already providing a ton of savings as such a service in the traditional finance world would cost 50k+$ - in Web3 less than 500$.

The same is true for hiring, payments, authenticating and outreach in the Web3 space. Wallets and the options that are attached to them are a powerful tool.

I think the savings and the faster verification of ideas is an important point.

Author: .scottm3
Content: Thanks again @Robin | DataUnion and @kaimeinke I think this gives me enough to go on for now at least! In terms of next steps it might be worth putting all of this thinking together into a document/blog post and share it here for review before publishing.

#TheYearOfScaling

• Yet data buyers can create value from it with analytics, AI modeling & more

🌊 All via the Ocean Market interface. Try it:
https://market.oceanprotocol.com/"

• They can access valuable, private data that was previously unavailable, which can lead to more accurate AI models. And w/o liability – they don’t see the data.
• They can also publish & monetize their algorithms. These can even stay private (!)"

"Businesses and entrepreneurs can quickly launch their own Ocean-powered data marketplace for their vertical. 

Ocean Compute-to-Data helps them further preserve their sellers’ privacy, and support more compute & AI flows."

https://oceanprotocol.com/technology/roadmap

We invite you to try out CtD, to explore, to stress-test, and to tell us how it goes! We welcome all feedback 💬"

Author: robinlehmann
Content:
Hey all, so to finalise the decision regarding price discussions, here is the poll:

1️⃣  Keep the policy as described in the pledge, no talk about the price of the Ocean token by Ambassadors, this is in line with the Ocean Protocol Foundation rule: Ambassadors ask themselves "Would an OPF team member do this?" before acting.
2️⃣  Change the policy to allow price talk and adapt the pledge accordingly. This allows Ambassadors to more actively promote the project in any way they see fit.

The poll will be open until Wednesday 8th of November 2021 at 4pm CEST, please only cast one vote.

Author: lrt8723
Content:
Hi everyone, 
As some of you may know I will have limited capacity to lead the Ocean Ambassador program over the next few weeks for personal reasons. During that time, the critical activities I was involved in will be covered by fellow senior Ambassadors. 

- @zippy1979 will take care of budget and finances. This process should move to Activity Farming and be managed as a team as early as February. In the meantime, Upkar will be in charge of validating with Ambassadors that they have completed their work, and preparing the list of payouts in OCEAN to Ambassadors.  

Upkar will also be the interim Program Lead, dealing with program improvements, being the liaison with the rest of the ecosystem, managing weekly updates in the OceanDAO meeting (this should be taken in turns by different ambassadors), and ensuring things run smoothly overall.

- @Andrea | Ocean Protocol will be the Community & Activity Lead, managing our group, the onboarding of new ambassadors and managing/coordinating the work of Ambassadors to ensure quality and timely deliveries.

- @Robin | DataUnion will prepare the Grant Proposal for OceanDAO R14, and keep co-approving transactions with me from our Gnosis safe.

Responsibilities and work in different WGs should be unaffected. I may have more time to allocate to the program than I anticipate, but I prefer to plan for the worst case and ensure that we have the right level of support for the group at all time.

Author: lrt8723
Content:
We had a great conversation yesterday with @Idiom | Ocean Protocol and Monica who leads the OPF Marcom, @Sheridan | Ocean Protocol, Noelle, @zippy1979, @Andrea | Ocean Protocol and @drprk.eth | Building stuff . They've helped get ambassadors' priorities straight; we shall: 
- Recruit new active members in OceanDAO (projects, voters, WG contributors), with local and targeted events
- Keep relaying partnership and other announcements from OPF, as well as support the creation of communication at a conceptual level (+ create specific artefacts based on the concepts developed to be used for outreach)
- There could be some budget for a campaign, e.g. video, specifically targeting ambassadors to grow the group and keep driving the visibility for the big announcements to come
- There will be a new WG set-up specifically for outreach, and we will join, together with the local programs. This is going to be where the latest news are shared, and wider coordination re communication will take place. It's exciting!

Besides, there are awesome things in the pipeline! 
--> One of the biggest event that's coming seen in the launch of Ocean V4!

So, we should get in the starting blocks to help make the V4 launch big, with dedicated messaging, articles, memes, ..etc.

Author: drprk.eth
Content:
Hello guys, at the #🪢︱ambassadors , Looking forward to some review of the Indian Ocean Outreach program. 

https://indian-ocean.gitbook.io/indian-ocean-outreach-program/

This essentially covers the roadmap and activities that we have set out to complete by end of this month.

Would be nice to have some feedback before I accelerate on a few promo activities. We have also placed a program in the name of 'Indian Ocean' ambassadors, who also have to complete the Ocean Academy. The aim is to have a lot of funneling outreach through the ambassadors from now on. We were glad to onboard @Gyan | Starknet Foundation/TPG as one of our first Ambassadors through both Academy as well as through the google form that we have mentioned in the Gitbook.

On a high-level, expecting some feedback on

- Overall information flow - is it sufficient? Giving a good intel of what's been played out so far?
- How the specific Ambassador program google form looks in line with Ocean 101 activities?
- We have not really decided on any promo-based activities yet for Indian ambassadors, but we will be sourcing it completely from the budget reserved for us during the R10 budget.

- Any other feedback that can help us?

**On a parallel note:** We are also working on a few workshop initiatives that will help folks convert better for the Ocean academy that is often regarded as 'too heavy' for complete beginners. We intend to follow the process, but would be happy to receive some feedback on all the above. In the future we also plan to work on some materials that will help people understand the Ocean academy better. The following article is an example of that.

https://medium.com/@indianoceandao/ocean-academy-guest-review-series-1f224e162f5b

Content:
Nothing is set in stone, at the moment. 

- As admittedly it's in a feedback phase at the moment and if there are any red-flags, would be happy to address it before venturing into any promos/activities (that we are deciding in line with a Final hackathon that is planned towards the end of Jan)

Author: doteth
doteth
Content:
Good morning @everyone, hope you all had a great WE!  ☀️

Quick update to keep you in the loop! 🚀 

As most of you may have realised from the ambassadors telegram group Q4/2021 saw a lot of planning and strategising. The vision of the Ambassador Program is to build an impactful global team that supports the growth of the Ocean Protocol ecosystem worldwide and, in order to achieve this, the Program needs to be well structured to welcome dozens, if not hundreds, of new ambassadors from each part of the world.
Ambassadors are now working hard to complete their tasks on time. The new program will be ready by end of this month and today we're sharing what will be its core: a brand new **Activity Farming and Rewards System.** 


**Activity Farming**. This is a list of activities that you as an ambassador can pick from and start working on anytime. https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1r-nG2Vjvicg_a3CUK9FPh2queAOYzhRwNYZyhvOuU4M/edit?usp=sharing
Once you find the activity you like and you are ready to start, add a Trello card with the name of the activity under the “Active” column. 


- **Rewards System**. We have introduced a mix of basic rewards and performance rewards to promote fairness, transparency, and to incentivise high-quality works. 
Base rewards are distributed at the end of each month upon meeting the minimum requirements, whilst Performance Rewards will be distributed upon meeting the predetermined targets at the end of the relevant period. 

NOTE:  If you would like to propose an initiative not present in the Activity Farming list, please add a Trello card in the “Activities Awaiting Confirmation” column and share details such as objectives, rewards request, ETA. Your initiative will then be evaluated by the AP team. 

The Activity Farming list is a living document, it will be reviewed monthly and improved as the program grows. We always welcome suggestions, so please share feedback by adding your comments in the Google Docs.

Happy farming! 🧑‍🌾 ❤️

Author: lrt8723
Content:
Hi DrPrk, thanks for sharing the Gitbook and the Medium article. I've checked them out and would have a few points of feedback:
1)    The Gitbook was a great idea, and it looks awesome. The Indian program is delivering on its objectives, which is excellent for everyone in the ecosystem!
2)    Handling ambassador recruitment through the Gitbook makes sense to build a vibrant Indian community, but it is not appropriate to recruit “Ocean Ambassadors” in my opinion. Why do I say that? 
a.    Because the Ocean Ambassadors have nearly completed a revamp of the onboarding process, and once the Ambassador website will be up, the Gitbook will be redundant. I would personally avoid duplicating processes/adding complexity and potential confusion for new ambassadors. 
b.    And because if we use the same process to recruit new members for different groups, we may end up facing unnecessary and unwishful competition across ‘branches’ of the program. 
c.    Finally, it could make sense to consider regional programs as standalone programs, that are not affiliated with the general ambassador group. All would meet and interact in a new Outreach WG, which I understand is in the process of being created. That’d be a great way to federate, share best practices and content, and loosely coordinate across all country programs, including Japan, Turkey, Greece, Nigeria, India, ..etc.

Author: lrt8723
Content:
3)    Great article on Ocean Academy. Having workshops on top is indeed helpful. It may need to be updated soon as we fine tune the launch of Ocean Academy V2, which was planned for end Dec ’21, but will be shipped end Jan ‘22. Here is the updated flow and content that I’m currently migrating to Github: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1RZaz5Aa9axjt6yGJgSHtIGTK9ambL4PDpHxUd-VJhog/edit?usp=sharing 

The content is easier to understand/digest, and is organized in a more logical flow for newcomers. In addition, the front-end + back-end have been updated and will be deployed at the same time as the content, so the user experience will be greatly improved with this V2.

Author: lrt8723
Content: Ocean Academy may be further improved, of course. Any specific observations, thoughts and feedback are good to take!

Author: drprk.eth
Content:
Super thanks for the feedback and for your time that you've taken @LRT 🙌 

1 & 2) Will go through with the feedback with some more considerations. I will also convey them to @Andrea | Ocean Protocol , I had a call earlier today where I expressed that the Ambassador 'program' per se will be an effective add-on with funneling mechanisms & remove duplicity, with more focus on managing traffic henceforth. I will work on your feedback and pass onto Andrea as well so it's in line with the revamped process. 

**But** I see why you mention that they need not be recruited. I will see if the Google form can be sunset with a different mechanism in place, adding redundant process can affect the UX of the general program. Rebranding it slightly different will be helpful in context of Outreach.

c) The outreach WG makes sense, will be a great place to have the processes separate from the Ambassador program in general.

3) Thanks for the feedback. Workshops will be planned in tandem with feedback on the process of V2 version of the academy as well. I will check the updated flow before discussing this again while planning the academy.

Author: lrt8723
Content:
Had a chat with @Andrea | Ocean Protocol and we discussed c) briefly. We should probably have a conversation on the future organization of the Ambassador program in the light of the growth of regional communities. 

Different projects handle things differently; Polkdadot, for example, have a very coordinated and hierarchical approach, with different heads, handling different regions and/or specialities within the group. This is also what Near has been successfully doing.

Author: lrt8723
Content: This would be something to discuss with @Idiom | Ocean Protocol , @Sheridan | Ocean Protocol , @zippy1979  and @Robin | DataUnion, and perhaps @BrucePon or @trentmc0 as well, with objective to establish a structure for Ambassadors doing Outreach work.

Author: drprk.eth
Content: Totally. Look forward to the conversations. Right now I will look to see that the current month sprint of the Indian outreach doesn't interfere with anything that is on the Ambassador's roadmap/plan of activities.

Author: drprk.eth
Content: I will read up more on Polkadot & Near system. Sounds interesting on how different programs can leverage off each other than necessarily clash with the overall aims for each project.

Author: doteth
Content:
Buongiorno @everyone 😃

We are feeling extremely happy to see lot of work coming to fruition. In fact, I am proud to finally announce the official revamp of the Ocean Protocol Ambassador Program (OPAP) 🚀 

Q4/2021 and beginning of Q1/2022 has seen a lot of planning, strategising and executing from every single ambassadors. The vision of the Ambassador Program is to build an impactful global team, that supports the growth of the Ocean Protocol ecosystem worldwide and, in order to achieve this, the Program needs to be well structured to welcome dozens, if not hundreds, of new ambassadors from each part of the world. This may, in the future, also involve having regional communities operating under the OPAP umbrella. 

Keeping our vision and needs in mind, the new program restructuring is now complete. I want to thank all Ambassadors and Ocean Core Team for their commitment to the program. Particularly I want to personally thank @LRT, @Robin | DataUnion , @blockchainlugano and @zippy1979 for supporting us in making this possible. 

Today I'm excited to announce:

- A revamped workspace to allow better coordination amongst ambassadors. The workspace is hosted on Notion, a tool that promotes team work and transparency. More details here: https://oceanambassadors.notion.site/Welcome-Aboard-cc9dbe2acbf44908aa7e8aa712a2b9f9

- A revamped onboarding process, where candidates will be guided through the ambassador website (Work in progress: http://oceanambassadors.community) -> Ocean 101 -> and eventually invited to an onboarding video call scheduled each week.

- The introduction of "Activity Farming". A smooth and efficient process for each ambassador to actively contribute to preapproved activities supporting OPF, and get rewarded based on two criteria: The deliverable itself & Performance. More details here: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1r-nG2Vjvicg_a3CUK9FPh2queAOYzhRwNYZyhvOuU4M/edit?usp=sharing

- An experimental reputation system that helps to promote engagement, increased contributions and team working within the OPAP. This system allows ambassadors to earn XP based on their contribution to the program - helping them stand out in our new Ambassador Leaderboard. More details here: https://oceanambassadors.notion.site/Leaderboard-f24b2461b60f4ce1970b255f7dd8767f

- OceanAcropolis. An open space for each ambassador to showcase their work, giving them (and everyone else) visibility across social media channels such as Twitter. More details here: https://oceanambassadors.notion.site/OceanAcropolis-750c110a7a234a7e86f577e7431f573c

- A revised Reward System to promote fairness, transparency, and to incentivise high-quality work. We have introduced a mix of basic rewards and performance rewards. Again, more details here: https://oceanambassadors.notion.site/OCEAN-Rewards-e803515ecda54c1f8fa5200af0343d40

- An open calendar where to find all OPAP meetings. As agreed with @Idiom | Ocean Protocol, all future Ambassadors meetings going forward will be publicly held in the #Ambassadors WG. More details here: https://www.notion.so/oceanambassadors/ff179fec09014037b29ac1bce067080a?v=47d781c17e0e426cafc48623f9398688

- An awesome video for everyone to quickly learn about Ocean Protocol and familiarise with the data economy. Sneak peek coming asap. 

Last but not least, we have also been working on our first AmbassadorDAO. However, this is still work in progress and shan’t reveal more at this time 🤐 

Plenty more is in the pipeline, and we're all looking forward to seeing what 2022 has for us!

#theyearofadoption

Happy farming! 👩‍🌾👨‍🌾 ❤️ 

Andrea

Author: drprk.eth
Content:
my 2 Ocean on the discussion (or do we have a 'cent' version of Ocean yet?)

Starting off with a general funda (feel free to critique).  For a p2e concept to work on the current concept, and to interface with a convenient Crypto-network component it has to be with a chain that doesn't disturb the end-user in anyway right?

So essentially that has to function with a network that is conducive for faster txns and lower fee, so from my birds eye view I see that Polygon, Solana are really popular on that front ~ which has happened as a result of marketing of course. Might be a reason why we have so many p2e games from a few suspect chains as a function of marketing/ecosystem push.

Do you have any line of thoughts to this @Robin | DataUnion on what you're developing?

Author: robinlehmann
Content:
Yeah, we are going to work with Polygon as we are using Ocean Protocol tech.
But also looking at Celo (mobile first proof of stake, eco friendly chain) and everything else where Ocean Protocol is available (e.g. Kusama, Polkadot via Moonbeam).
We are suffering from having our pool on Ethereum mainnet for a long time now and will change that very soon when V4 comes out 🙂

Author: drprk.eth
Content: Cool that's great to know. So I suppose at the end of the day when you're thinking of p2e Project you'd only be looking at how users engage or would that be something that has to be very exclusive from a particular ecosystem

Author: robinlehmann
Content:
No, in the end it is important that they have an identity in the form of a wallet or a SSI identity but also the option to receive part of the value being created from the p2e project they are participating in.
So we could have chains connected where there is no data asset being offered but the value created is just transfered there from another chain.
And our backend is very flexible in regard to the identification scheme used.

Author: drprk.eth
Content: Ah i see. So the p2e element would be web3 specific nonetheless? Or if a person has an SSI identity that is agnostic to web3 products, can they still participate in your p2e product?

Author: drprk.eth
Content: Don't mind me if you think this is a lot of questions. I'm just curious on some alphas and to learn something new 😄

Author: robinlehmann
Content:
It is important that this person can be identified to make the e part of p2e available to them - a wallet is a great piece of technology that enables that 🙂 but where that is possible/can be depends on where the value is created.
In DataUnion's case - where is the data being offered via compute-to-data and where are the algorithms being used? that is where the value is created and this value is then split to the participants and made available to their SSI/wallet identity.

Author: drprk.eth
Content: Alright that makes sense. From the overall funda, It's so commendable to see that we have a p2e within our ecosystem that is evolving to be chain-agnostic (courtesy ocean-stack) and web3 native. Not a lot of people try to start off with that. I know Manan is also working on Oceanverse game so looking forward to both.

Author: lrt8723
Content:
The first article is spot on IMO - governance minimization is key. I believe they overstate "consensus" which relates to day-to-day operations and understate "strategic governance" which relates to deep gov redesign, vision or objective changes of the systems when needed. 

The Gitcoin presentation is fascinating. I wish someone old these guys that data should be expressed in % terms rather than absolute number of survey respondents.. but it doesn't change the value of the insights gathered. Brilliant. I think we can relate to this comment re pain points "The biggest pain point are people who want to help but need to be helped to be able to help 🙂 So, for now only very assertive people find something to do."

Author: lrt8723
Content:
The FEI protocol article provides some interesting thoughts on a particular implementation of "Optimistic Governance". Our intended implementation in "Activity Farming" is more flat, and is handled "after-the-facts" 

This means that ***requests for $OCEAN rewards are made by the Ambassador working on an activity only once the activity has been delivered or once the activity performance can be attested. Activities do not need to be pre-aligned*** prior to working on them, as long as they are in our Activity Farming list, and the deliverable complies with our Ambassador pledge.

Upon submission, ***by default activities are approved and paid***. If another Ambassador has doubts and wants to review the activity, the reviewing Ambassador should state so, which will trigger a review process in which Ambassadors should discuss and conclude whether the activity should be paid or not.

Author: lrt8723
Content:
More on Optimistic Governance: https://docs.gyro.finance/governance/primitives/optimistic-approval and https://ournetwork.substack.com/p/our-network-deep-dive-2 --- this is all based on Web3 stacks, but we could learn faster by handling things off-chain, iterating fast to learn and implementing on-chain when a solution makes sense. 

We don't really have much to fear about GEV exploits as we will most likely never have deep pockets, and our purpose is not monetary. But of course we want to avoid as many obvious flaws in our governance processes as possible

Author: doteth
Content:
Thank you Bhalisa! I’m interested to discuss this proposal with other ambassadors as well. As of now I see 2 approaches: 

- centralisazion of articles into the OPAP medium account (with no audience and exposure yet) 

- publishing articles on ambassadors’ medium account leveraging on their audience/community.

While I prefer the first approach as it can be seen as a more long term strategy, it won’t really bring many benefits to Ocean Protocol in the short term (particularly V4). The second approach doesn’t bring any benefits to OPAP but it does help OPF getting more exposure. 

Hence the question, is there a way you see both solutions coexisting or are they mutually exclusive? Happy to hear other ambassadors too

Ref. Proposal: https://oceanambassadors.notion.site/Ambassadors-Medium-Curation-Articles-8d854ab16c924ce0982bb389e3894f32

Author: bhalisa
Content: If we are even considering having an Ambassadors Medium page, a long term approach is inevitable. An audience is built. Leveraging off of each others' audiences is a good start. There's only one approach here @Andrea | Ocean Protocol; that is building our audience by leveraging off of individuals' audiences. Also looking forward to others' opinions.

Author: zippy1979
Content: Regarding the meme payment in the Activity Farming, if we want to move away from subject discussions on whether a meme is of high enough "quality" both in terms of originality and humour, we would need to heavily weight the reward towards performance rather than have $100 for base.

Author: zippy1979
Content:
So for March I would suggest a $10 max base reward for memes (same no matter how many are submitted i.e. $10 for one meme or if 20 memes are submitted $10 max payout) with a $150 performance reward (uncapped) for every qualifying delivery.
E.g. If you submit 7 memes, you would get paid $10 total, and later if 2 go viral and are widely shared (to be defined) you could get an additional $150 for each of them, total payout $310.

Author: nosedive2moon
Content:
Hi Ambassador - I made a proposal to change the reward structure for translation articles and put it into activity farming
At the moment its 30$ Base reward for articles > 500 words and 1000$ Base reward for articles > 1000 words. 

The problem is : The most interesting and relevant articles from OP are mainly above 1500 - 2000 words. But at the moment the work/reward ratio for articles slightly above 1000 words is the best. So the motivation to translate that kind of articles instead of the ones that are much more interesting & relevant is much higher. By raising the reward for this the motivation to translate that articles will rise. 

I suggest adding 3 categories according to the work load: 

> 1500 words = 150 USD Base Rewards + 450 USD Bonus Rewards for 1k Impressions within 3 Month
> 2000 words = 200 USD Base Rewards + 600 USD Bonus Rewards for 1k Impressions within 3 Month
> 2500 words = 250 USD Base Rewards + 750 USD Bonus Rewards for 1k Impressions within 3 Month

Author: nosedive2moon
Content: The rewards are just scaled in relation to the recent reward structure for 1000 words

Author: wally0221
Content:
Allow me this slight hint, as I am German: We're in a new world. We're Web3. I think it's more than appropriate to strip off the last remaining TradBiz / enterprise ties (this is aligned with Trent) and remove the "Sie" and replace it with a "Du" in our German translations. 

Context for non-German speakers: 
"Sie" is close to the old English word "thee", a (very) polite way of addressing the reader, while "Du" is close to the English "You". 

It reads and looks intuitive, compared to all stuff I read on Blockchain and Web3. 

Just my 2cents, your call of course.

Author: doteth
Content:
📚  **EASY POLL - Quick Guide** 📚 

- With the /Poll Command you can easily create polls. Normal polls have no time limit. A poll can be either a simple yes/no poll or a poll with up to 20 custom answers. When you create a Poll, you can choose who is allowed to vote

- With the /TimePoll Command you can easily create polls with time limit. In this case a poll can run for a maximum of 7 days.

**Useful commands to use: **

allowedrole - to restrict voting to certain roles 
text - to add a long description, perhaps to give context and introduce the reason of the poll
time - to set a time limit to the poll

Author: zippy1979
Content: Hej OPAP Fam, some good news, @Scott M3 is moving his Campfire podcast over to OPAP.

Author: zippy1979
Content:
**What does this mean?**
Scott has been running a high quality outreach project called Ocean Missions. As part of this he has produced a podcast called Campfire, (I recommend you take a listen to the Richard Blythman episode in particular)
https://www.oceanmissions.com/campfire/episodes/
He will continue to run the podcast, however it will now be delivered as part of our OPAP Activity Farming and as such be **co-branded as a project sponsored by OPAP.**

Author: zippy1979
Content:
I would also like to add a new activity to the farming, this is to encourage regular and consistent production of content, rewards would only be given in the months that content is produced. So if you are an Ambassador that can consistently deliver and produce podcast content, you can apply for assistance with the hosting costs.
**Name:**
Podcast Infrastructure Support
**Requirement:**
Minimum 5 episodes already produced, minimum of 1 episode released in the month of application, Professional Podcast only
**Reward:**
$50
**Performance Reward:**
10000 Downloads monthly for an extra $50

Author: zippy1979
Content:
An important note for @Ambassador 
We are about to do the disbursements for April deliveries, which when completed, will deplete the treasury. We have submitted a funding proposal for OceanDAO R17. However until new funds are disbursed from the DAO we will not be able to pay the bounties for activities that people may deliver.
**I would ask for your patience and need to request that activities be paused for May until we have confirmation of funding.**
You may ask why we are in this situation, the answer is simple. A combination of the recent market drop affecting the value of the mOCEAN we hold, as well as many of the team overdelivering (and reaching performance targets) in April means that we have needed to pay out more than usual.

Author: zippy1979
Content:
🚨 @Ambassador 🚨

Hello OPAP Friends 

The OceanDAO reconcilliation is now complete and we did not make the funding this round despite attracting more than 1.3m votes. This again means that we will need to pause the Activity Farming until we can resolve the funding issue. I personally will not be drawing any rewards, until this issue is resolved. Everything else needs to be paused (other than Twitter which we need to maintain for visibility and growth). For the activities already submitted we will review them in the month end Activity Farming Review as usual, however how the treasury will be dispersed, will need to be voted on by the members of OPAP. I will ask that when you cast your votes you consider the long term health of the program rather than short term personal gains.

I am in discussions with our advisors how best to handle this situation going forward, applying for funds in every single OceanDAO funding round rather than once per quarter, is not a sustainable funding model for an Ambassadors program. We will need to make changes no matter what.

How we address this and create a sustainable funding model will be worked on and shared with you for comment and then pushed forward. Anyone who wishes to help with this process is welcome to reach out to myself or @blockchainlugano  and your input will be appreciated.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador So here is the link in Notion regarding the blogs.  https://oceanambassadors.notion.site/OceanDAO-Blog-0c71c4867e584aa2bad2f58d7de024ed 

**Please read the instructions before jumping in.** There are samples in the document to give you an idea of what the deliverable should be like.

💥  If you have not written before I highly recommend submitting a sample to us before tackling this.

✅ Some of us have already spoken and I am happy for you to go ahead and tackle a blog post. 

📌 Reminder, all blogs will go through a draft review. 

🫂 We are a big team and truly support one another. That being said, there are deadlines and quality standards, and if we feel the blog is not quite publishable, we will likely reassign it to another writer.

🤝 Your notes (we recommend using Google Docs) are important to us as well as OPF so they *must* be posted in Discord

👀  You will contact the funded DAO projects using the provided contact details from the DAO applications; you **must** CC op_ambassadors@protonmail.com in **all** correspondence with subjects.

💗 Let me know if you have any questions! Feel free to post them here for everyone or DM me if you feel more comfortable.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador 

To clarify writing about the OceanDAO blogs. 

1) OP Ambassador email MUST be cc'd in ALL correspondence with DAO grantee in order to have proof of their responses and verify context and writing within the draft that can then be used for the final product. We have received sparse to no communication nor answers in this delivery chain.

2) The blog post is attributed to the writer or the Ambassadors, this is the writers choice. HOWEVER, seeing as this is a remunerated activity, OPF needs to have first publishing rights to this and I kindly ask Ambassadors'
--- to NOT publish their blog posts BEFORE OPF
--- to wait until the draft has been verified and edited, and is good for publication. 

3) Again, if you have questions as to how this works please reach out to me or @zippy1979 .

🙏

Author: kitblake
Content:
👋 Hey Ambassadors, our team presented our Streaming Data Asset from Grant Round 19 to the community. We would appreciate testing and we welcome feedback! The team includes myself and @okpo.e and @databeatle (who are also Ambassadors :)

• For context you could read the User Story: https://kitblake.substack.com/p/data-streams-like-rain

• Our User Guide is at: https://github.com/chaineresearch/datastreams/wiki/UserGuide

• The UI of our fork is here: https://oceanmarket-datastreams.netlify.app/

• Known issues are in the Github Issue Tracker. You're welcome to open an issue. The code is at: https://github.com/chaineresearch/datastreams/tree/v0.1

**Testing**
Please try to create a new Streaming Data Asset. We used this Helsinki public transportation API as an example stream source:
https://realtime.hsl.fi/realtime/vehicle-positions/v2/hsl
Here is the API Docs URL for the stream: https://www.hsl.fi/en/hsl/open-data

Author: igork_ldn
Content:
Hi @kitblake I will focus on the first point for now. Storytelling. I understand the concept. The story is interestingly told. Maybe the comic will be interesting? There is a lot of action. One question. Why is the main character's name Volodymyr?  

If you create a text and publish it at a certain time and under certain circumstances. Readers will always have connotations of what is happening around them. I suggest choosing a more neutral name for these times. So that readers can fully focus on your story without context. Contexts create metaphors.

Author: kitblake
Content:
@Igor K and @Zamirana, thanks for your reactions! I see now that giving the main character the same first name as the Ukrainian president may not have been amusing and proved a distraction. So I’ve changed the name. But I haven’t used Alice or Bob. Here’s the thinking.

That Wikipedia article was illuminating. I wasn’t thrilled with Alice or Bob because they have personalities. Now I’ve learned that their personalities were defined in an "After Dinner Speech" in 1984. The main character of our User Story doesn’t fit those personalities. He’s a developer type.

Since those early days more characters have been added to the Alice & Bob story. There’s Eve, who’s an eavesdropper, and Mallory, who’s malicious. There’s also “Ivan The Honourable” who was invented in 2002.

'Ivan' is a fitting name for a dev. It connotes the right mindset. Someone who’s honourable and concerned about the quality of the code. The name is also not tied to any specific country. Could even be American, like Alice & Bob are.

Thus the main character in our User Story is now Ivan, and I think it’s a real improvement. Thanks for your feedback, it proved valuable. 🙏

Author: vkpatva
Content:
I was just exploring in what ways can we integrate a DAO to work with Ocean Protocol and Data assets. What are the possible actions that we can take through a DAO on our DataNFTs and datatokens?

I have read about Fractional NFTs in the docs, where a group of people can hold a single NFT and govern actions related to that DataNFT and its datatokens. 
a) how can we implement this? Is there a smart contract (DAO) that is the owner of the minted DataNFT and Datatokens? and the actions that we take on the Data asset (updating, minting datatokens, managing roles) are voted for on the DAO contract and then sanctioned? 
b) Is there any helpfull repo or implementation of a working DAO in the ocean tools as of now?
c) Is this the only use case of implementing a DAO with Ocean Contract? or we can use a DAO elsewhere with Ocean Protocol?

Content:
@Ambassador 
End of week reminder & wrap up:

✅ Please have all deliverables for this weeks bounties posted in the Acropolis by tomorrow, Friday, at midnight CET.

🗓️ Please make a note in your schedule to try and make our next OPAP meeting, on Thursday April 06, 17:00 CET in Discord #voice-channel https://discord.gg/b6bCbRgU. (Ambassador voice no longer exists)

The meetup is entitled 'Future Initiatives & Reflections' . What we aim to cover is upcoming use of Snapshot to use as a tool to vote on certain deliverables as the OPAP community, as well as what will be considered worthy of bounty payments outside the scope of what is currently posted. We will also discuss possible future bounties and want to hear your ideas as well.

:Oceancopy: As per next weeks objectives, let's try and maintain the momentum of focusing on OPF official events in Discord with the objective of getting more people curious to onboard to using Ocean.

Have a great Friday and weekend sailors! 🌊

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador 
Team mates. We really need to get a handle on what's being posted in social media comms. 

I am taking an inordinate amount of time 1:1 to ensure you understand how the Ocean tech stack works, what it can and cannot do, etc.

BUT...some posts are simply inaccurate. If you have doubts about your post please ask in our channel before posting. 

Inaccurate data about this technology is worse than no posting. It is simply misleading to the public, and if you put Ambassador in your profile the assumption is you know, on a base level, the workings here.

This is proving to be untrue. Please read and review the massive amount of free writings put out by the OPF team, on Twitter, YouTube, github etc. To deep dive and come back to ask questions if you have them.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
If you would like to have your material reviewed before posting in regards solely to the TECH and validity of your statements, not images or quality (note this will slow down the workflow as we are not designed to do this microgranular editing) please post it here https://www.notion.so/oceanambassadors/Works-in-Progress-33a48efcd57a417395bf0b72824ebdcf and one of us will get back to it when we can. 

I invite ALL ambassadors to take a look at this to help one another out in the spirit of this program. There need not be finger wagging or unconstructive call outs, but if you understand something is incorrect, you can help us out by dropping notes in the 'notes' column for your fellow crewmate. Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
Ok team, we took  time to go through the bounties delivered last week. Really chewed on this which is why today is Wednesday and normally this is done by Monday, but I am remaining shellshocked that 95% of the work put in is simply incorrect or incoherent, some on a large scale. None of you will win bounties this way, so IMO really read and ask questions to understand how this works, or you will be wasting your precious time for zero reward:

Here is an example, see if you can spot an issue, and this is taken from the top 2 threads submitted (good job btw, because it is nearly there!).

Part of a posted thread: 
Ocean Templates is an open-source toolkit from @oceanprotocol that provides a complete answer to common issues experienced in #blockchain dApp development. 

Reasoning this is not of useable quality: 
Ocean Protocol does provide a set of tools and infrastructure to help developers build decentralized applications (dApps) centered around data marketplaces. This includes the usage of templates that *facilitate* standardized data exchange agreements.

However, it's important to note that Ocean Protocol and its tools are specifically tailored to data sharing, buying, and selling use-cases. They may not address all the "common issues" experienced in general blockchain dApp development, but they do indeed provide significant benefits for those particular use-cases.

With that in mind, a more accurate statement might be:

Ocean Templates, part of the @oceanprotocol toolkit, provides a comprehensive solution to common challenges experienced in blockchain-based data marketplace development. This thread will inform developers how it can reduce complications and accelerate time-to-market for developing data-centric dApps.

:OPAPShield: **Always be sure to research the specific functionalities and scope of a particular toolkit or platform before making broad claims about its applicability and benefits.**

Author: due_writer
Content:
Thanks for the response. Here we go:

1 - Image Description:
A captivating image depicting a vast ocean stretching to the horizon, symbolizing the sea of data waiting to be explored. The image showcases a beautiful sunset, casting warm hues of orange and pink across the tranquil water. In the distance, a shipyard emerges, representing the gateway to innovative possibilities.

2 - Image Description:
An image showcasing a digital landscape with interconnected data nodes floating in the air. These nodes are connected by vibrant lines, representing the seamless integration between data assets, blockchain, and DeFi tools. The image illustrates the power of Ocean in unlocking the value hidden within data and enabling effortless data publishing and consumption.

3 - Image Description:
A vibrant image displaying an animated shipyard bustling with activity. The shipyard is filled with futuristic vessels, each representing a start-up ready to embark on their journey. The ships are diverse in design and color, symbolizing the variety of entrepreneurial ventures that Ocean Shipyard attracts. The image conveys a sense of excitement, opportunity, and the promise of new horizons.

4 - Image Description:
An artistic illustration showcasing the merging of decentralized finance (DeFi) and data on the high seas. The image features a dynamic scene with data NFTs floating above the ocean waves, intertwining with financial elements like tokens and yield symbols. The illustration represents the integration of Ocean's data protocols with DeFi, emphasizing the potential for innovative financial products and the creation of new markets.

Author: due_writer
Content:
5 - Image Description:
A collaborative image portraying entrepreneurs engaging in brainstorming sessions with the esteemed members of the Ocean core team. The image captures a roundtable discussion in a modern meeting room, with individuals passionately exchanging ideas and sketching on whiteboards. The atmosphere is one of collaboration, mentorship, and guidance, showcasing the partnership between start-ups and the experienced Ocean core team.

6 - Image Description:
An image illustrating the progressive journey of start-ups within Ocean Shipyard. The image shows a ship sailing across a map, symbolizing the immersive voyage embarked upon by start-ups alongside the Ocean core team. The map features markers indicating milestones, such as the development of an initial Minimum Viable Product (MVP) or beta version. The image signifies progress, growth, and the nurturing of ideas within the Ocean ecosystem.

7 - Image Description:
A captivating image showcasing a captain's wheel surrounded by a compass, a pen, and an application form. This image represents the process of charting a course to Ocean Shipyard. The captain's wheel signifies the role of entrepreneurs in steering their projects, while the compass symbolizes guidance and direction. The pen and application form represent the comprehensive application process, highlighting the importance of a clear use case and deployment potential.

8 - Image Description:
A visionary image portraying a shoreline where data seamlessly transforms into valuable assets. The image features a bridge connecting the land and the ocean, representing the transformative power of Ocean Shipyard. Data elements, represented by colorful particles, flow from the land to the ocean, symbolizing the expansion of the data economy. The image signifies the boundless opportunities for innovation and growth that await those who dare to dream and embark on this revolutionary journey.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador 
:OPAPShield: We have in the last few months onboarded quite a few ambassadors which is a huge success for us and we have many more coming in. Although our Academy and requisite activities for onboarding are quite thorough, it generally takes time to fully grasp the many technical aspects of Ocean Protocol.

🤝 We are looking to begin fostering greater communication within regions and within our crew, and I highly recommend looking at the Meet the Team page in Notion where you can find fellow ambassadors in your own language or region. This would be a great help as many of you that have been here longer can assist in mentoring newer ambassadors that may have some questions or are seeking clarity.

📣 When it makes sense for the OPAP program, we are happy to support local meetups IF objectives and deliverables are clear. But the first step in this is to find fellow ambassadors and begin discussion, really be clear on the Ocean Protocol ecosystem and technologies,  and then you can reach out to @zippy1979 or @blockchainlugano for advancing this activity.

🧠 Also, don't forget a huge benefit to you ambassadors is each other. Many successful projects have been realized by ambassadors getting together, ideating and building (DeltaDAO, Dataunion, etc). There is a wealth of information between all the brains here, and we would love to see you using OPF's tools in creating amazing products for the decentralized forward thinking web3 space.

Author: beason82
Content: Hi guys, re: this section from https://oceanprotocol.com/technology/compute-to-data

Author: beason82
Content:
I have a friend who works in data protection who says this is incorrect:

"So it's 'Special category data' that's afforded extra protection and where the data is 'stored' is irrelevant, it's where it is 'processed'. Also GDPR doesn't require data to stay on 'European soil', GDPR applies to the 'EU' and there are jurisdictions which are afforded 'adequacy' that are outside of the 'EU'. There are circumstances where you could transfer special category data outside of the EU if you have the appropriate mechanisms in place"

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador 
Regarding the new PFP's, those of you that have claimed your ambassador badge will have already seen that yours has been automatically upgraded to the correct one.

We will be pinning a message here to explain the correspondence of badge upgrades to XP points and deliverables. There will also be a message in #🪢︱treasure-hunter covering this.

The new onboarding of ambassadors will now be for participants to have discourse and participation in the treasure-hunter channel, and it is up to US, the ambassadors and OPF core team to reward them with upvoting QUALITY comments, observations, scope of OPF in order to award them points. Each 💯 is worth 3 XP points. Please award these only if the participation warrants it. (gm, emojis, basic comments etc do not count). They will work their way up to 99 points of which then they will be prompted to apply to become an ambassador.

Ambassadors can also upvote one another and this is ONLY a part of you climbing up the ladder, bounties and referrals will be part of it (details will be pinned here in the channel)

The XP bot is to launch very soon, will let you all know when it does.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
In order to start using the #🪢︱treasure-hunter I need to set your starting XP points as you are all @Ambassador 's and are not starting at 0. Please show up and drop a message or emoji so I may assign them to you. 

The XP points works in order to raise your score as you work your way to a higher role. Points are a part of it, bounty deliverables and successful outreach another. Visual cards will be pinned in the channel very soon.

Only Ambassadors and OPF core team may award XP points to anyone in the channel. I ask you to be CAREFUL when awarding them, they are merit based and only valuable, interesting and thought provoking messages should be awarded. 

✅ You can award the member by responding with the 💯 emoji. The rest of the emoji's will not award points so feel free to use those freely.

✅ XP points are awarded in value increments of 3 per emoji.

✅ Ambassador Leads have the capability of removing points, hopefully we should not have to do so often!

✅  You may check your points by calling the XP bot using `/check-xp`

✅ We are a crew and need to work together as such, working towards the same objective. Award those you feel really deserve it, don't be stingy, nor don't award flippantly.

✅ We want this channel to stimulate conversation, learning and action. You may of course use it to your liking, talking about alpha in the data world, web3, the data economy, etc. This is supposed to be fun.

It has taken us a long time to get here, the bot was built for OPAP and we hope this makes our activities fun and a bit competitive and more engaging for you. We will quite soon be running simple and fun bounties in the channel. 

If the bot stops working (as I am not always on) please DM @blockchainlugano  or @zippy1979 to resolve.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
Team, I deleted some posted messages about the retweet. From now on I will post these in these requests in the #🪢︱treasure-hunter channel and feel free to ping when completed there, I'd like to keep our channel fairly clean.

We already have a few new interested applicants for the program, so they will be joining the channel and begin their XP journey to get to 99 and be prompted to do a few additional steps in order to onboard. In the meantime please interact and help them discover all things Ocean Protocol. This is the objective, for newbies to understand how Ocean works before they become Ambassadors, and we need your help.

Those of you who assist meaningfully and respond with accurate and complete responses will also be rewarded by the community with XP points. The idea is circular. Let's prompt discussions and deep dives.

Thank you crew! ⚓

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador finally, last week's bounty submissions have been judged. perhaps for the first time in 5 months, we do not have ANY bounty winners. 🙄 

A few of you put forth some great material. Some notes:

*Be sure what you write is accurate and factual. When in doubt, ask core team in the main channel.

*Be original. A few lines of fresh content go much further than...'Did you know Ocean offers compute-to-data'. This has been tweeted for years.

*TikTok videos. Remember, winners are being added directly into OPF's account, not shared, so it has to be something OPF would themselves make. Think corporate, think funny, think timeless, think global.

I recognize the hurdles presented in these bounties and am looking forward to releasing more accessible ones very soon.

Author: denkcryptoo12
Content:
Do you think Ocean Protocol's partnership with Moonbeam has had much of an impact? @Ambassador 

My thoughts on it: 

The collaboration with Moonbeam Network signifies Ocean Protocol's expansion to the Polkadot blockchain. Initial integration will empower users to seamlessly "publish, stake, and buy" data within Polkadot's ecosystem. Assets from both Ethereum mainnet and Moonbeam will eventually coexist within the Ocean Market, a platform for data discovery and exchange. Enhanced privacy features, network bridging, and liquidity sharing are also on the horizon.

Trent McConaghy, Co-Founder of Ocean Protocol, highlights the alignment of Ocean's multi-blockchain vision with Polkadot's interoperability focus. Moonbeam's Ethereum compatibility makes it a logical starting point for Ocean's Polkadot venture. 

The Moonbeam team is constantly working to simplify the implementation process for Ethereum developers who want to migrate to Polkadot. Ocean Protocol chose Moonbeam as an extension point because of its unrivaled compatibility. The Ocean team can now utilize their existing Ethereum smart contracts to access the new and growing Polkadot ecosystem.

Author: denkcryptoo12
Content:
Also wanted to get on the topic of UTU's AI-driven trust infrastructure with Ocean ones


UTU's AI-driven trust infrastructure will assimilate data providers, consumers, datasets, and entities' interactions to construct comprehensive trust profiles. Moreover, Ocean users can rate and review these entities, all contributing to a dynamically analyzed trust signal.

This approach elevates trust and transparency within Ocean Market, minimizing transactional friction. Users can seamlessly access quality datasets from reliable providers, utilize data for analysis or stake, and avoid risks like rug pulls, fostering a more secure and reliable ecosystem

Furthermore, the UTU protocol rewards users for providing precise ratings and reviews while safeguarding their data privacy. Collaborating with Ocean will streamline the process for UTU users to monetize their data on Ocean Market as data providers. Users retain complete authority over shared data, deciding which to monetize and its usage terms.

The partnership aims to facilitate data exchange between their protocols. This entails incorporating publicly-available, on-chain UTU data like endorsements into Ocean Market, procuring relevant Ocean Market datasets for the UTU protocol, and analyzing datasets to generate UTU recommendations and insights.

Author: kreigdk
Content:
I think

The collaboration between Ocean Protocol and Moonbeam is important. It helps Ocean Protocol become part of another blockchain. It gives people more ways to work with data. It also allows them to make bets based on that data. All in all, these are new opportunities for Ocean Protocol.
Working with UTU is also a good thing. They are using artificial intelligence to help people trust each other when sharing data. So Ocean Market becomes a place to find safe and quality data. And UTU helps users make money from their data on Ocean Market.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador 
Regarding bounty round 36 (week before last) we had a major issue, and I was not able to look at them until mid-week this past week. Nearly ALL of the submissions were good  EXCEPT one major issue. Nearly all of you mention 'data is safe with secure data storage' !!! 
This is of course incorrect. Ocean has NOTHING to do with storage and you should all know that, one it was in the quiz to get in and two, by now with all you are reading so much about Ocean that this should be clear. Storage is up to the providor, and Ocean has no access to it, nor can verify what is in the data. 
So no, there were no bounty winners as the few that did have a correct thread were not written strongly enough to publish or they were about data farming which we agreed is not on the subject list.

Moving forward I will again be having 1:1 calls with all potential ambassadors as I once did to assure key factors are understood.  Will be reading this weeks submissions today.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador 
Reminder on granting XP's in the #🪢︱treasure-hunter channel. Please grant points only for really interesting, high quality or original thoughts, or to new entrants who are making an effort to understand this. 
Repetitive answers or contributions should not be getting awarded multiple times. That in essence kinda games the system. I know it's frustrating and a long road to get XP's, but don't forget even us ambassadors that have been here years started at 100 when this was shipped. 
It's not a race, it's about contribution and quality. We all know Ocean is not a simple protocol, and we put these concepts in place to help people learn. We are working hard on finding novel and actionable ways to earn XP's.

Thanks for your understanding. Also because, core team does not have time to award points, so it is entirely up to us. WE control who earns, and we shouldn't abuse this power.

Author: doteth
Content:
Hey everyone

Just wanted to drop here a little hack for the Twitter Impression campaign starting tomorrow. 

You can try these techniques to farm more impressions 😎

- Add hashtags with high viewerships. #AI could be an example, but there are more. Check the trending section and see if any of them fits. Remember too many hashtags are penalized by X so you want to select them carefully 

- Replies to posts with high views can be another way to farm impressions 

- Tagging other accounts can provide more visibility to your post. Add context to your post such that it makes sense to tag other companies.

- Pin your post to your profile to ensure you gain views every time someone visits your profile

- Sharing your tweet on Reddit or other social media can hugely increase viewrships

- the timing of your post/comment matters

I’d suggest to try them all to see which one works best for you. There may also be other techniques that I didn’t mention yet. 

If you get stuck do let me know! Happy weekend 😄

Author: feno1486
Content:
@blockchainlugano I'm filling out this form with a vote, and the question arose, why do we even need this strange voting? Why can’t the winner be chosen in a normal way, by an objective and uninterested person from the team, like you for example?
This vote raises huge doubts:
1. To evaluate the quality of a written text, the examiner must have knowledge and he must read the text carefully and thoughtfully. That is, if a person did not participate in creating the content, then he must first read the material, understand it, and then check works. Who will do this?
2. Where are the guarantees that people who have a voice will even read what is written there? But they won’t give ratings randomly, based on just one picture, for example.
3. In fact, voters are rivals; the right to vote is a tool for various manipulations.
4. Variation with the formation of voting teams.
5. In the ambassador program, people communicate with each other, some closer, some further. It is clear that each person is not objective by default and will give more rating to his friend.

I think we can find more reasons to doubt. I just can’t understand why we need to break something that worked?

Author: kreigdk
Content: I agree with Feno. While voting is important, it may not be a sufficiently reliable assessment method, as there is a risk of manipulation, such as voting for oneself or for friends.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
I am reflecting on the entire week of voting, via metrics and via quality vote.

Two hiccups. 
The winning bounty on metrics was actually @Qazim if you go by numbers. His tweet looks like it was taken down from being flagged at a certain point and thus was not eligible in the end. There was also a bug on Postmint, now fixed.

The tool spread with google docs led to 2 threads not making in the community vote, as submissions drop automatically from postmint when the threshold is not met. So they were added late, and went unvoted on.

A potential workaround is:
Condense BOTH metrics and quality on Postmint via 1 bounty. Community (those accepted in the campaign, meaning ambassadors) can rate the tweet directly in Postmint. So at that point both are evaluated at the same time, we can weight value to metrics vs rating.

We can as usual payout top 3. This reduces tool spread, and balances those who might play unfair with analytics, and rewards quality in one go.

Feedback? drop in https://discord.com/channels/612953348487905282/1166990250338431046/1166995018590990476

Author: stip11
Content:
I also want to note why the system with metrics of views will not work correctly in any case, if we are talking about honesty and transparency, if in this case everything is clear, then in the future, if we again face such a situation (I hope very much that it is not) it will be impossible to prove whether the post was tipped by a participant or not because all accounts are open and posts too and thus any participant can be "thrown" out of the contest by large views even if he did not do it, there is no way to prove guilt or innocence here

To avoid this, should also rely on other indicators such as likes, reposts and engaged accounts.

I don't think this will happen, but if we have already had a situation like this in the first contest, we need to consider all options

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
Just to clarify, Postmint has two types of "ratings". 

1/ Score = derived from Twitter metrics (impressions & engagements" )

2/ Rating = from the manual rate bar on the tweet card 

The score determines the payout and who is first place 
The rating slightly influences the score  

Campaign participants can rate the tweets only before scoring (end of the epoch) . This is active now.

Content: Sir, if I understand correctly, please correct me, @George(Will never DM you first). In this method, one needs to like a post, and in return, they will receive a like. Many websites operate based on this strategy. To participate, you simply sign up and provide your account details. Then, you can select what you want in return: a retweet, a like, or a follow. The website uses a points system. To illustrate, let's say I like or retweet a tweet and gain 100 points. I can then use these 100 points to get what I want, such as followers. If someone follows me, I can choose to give them some of my points, let's say 5 points. So, those who need points can do the same as I did in the beginning to collect points. Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador @Elite Ambassador 
We continuously strive to keep our program fair and solid for everyone involved. It is evidenced in our pledge, our small team, our family like environment since the inception of the program.

Using Postmint, a new platform, has allowed us to try and automate certain aspects of our bounty program.

The last round is still not ready to be paid out due to ongoing questions we have with scoring and how to mitigate those attempting to game the system.

As a reminder, we ask that you abide by your signed pledge and participate in the program as an honest person. Doing anything less harms the program, delays payment, derails program enhancement, and just makes the program fail. 

Historically we had very few ambassadors since we value quality over quantity. We still believe this, but have relaxed onboarding a bit compared to 3 years ago in an attempt to get a more group feeling and inclusive not exclusive community. 

I encourage anyone here to use our channel to openly discuss issues you feel need to be addressed. And if you feel more comfortable please DM them to me and I will repost here anon. to stimulate discussion. We are a crew working together, there is no set 'captain' per se, let's move the boat in the right direction together.
