Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
@Ambassador @Elite Ambassador 

I finalized last weeks Postmint rewards. I had to manually adjust for a few things, and scores do not reflect metrics as its impossible to do. So, this is a one off but a lesson here.

*The best performing threads did not win. They should've been kicked out but I left them in the competition, but choosing Ocean's own marketplace is a lazy move. The objective was to think outside the box and either find a ecosystem partner or invent one.

*Due to not being able to score metrics, the points were arbitrarily awarded, in fairness to following instructions, and then best performing.

Author: himas.
Content: Kick out for what? what a lazy step, I spent 3 hours searching for information that best fits the wording of the question, going through all possible applications. And Ocean Market fits the theme best; other applications fit the wording worse and do not fulfill some of the conditions presented in the theme.

Author: himas.
Content: After spending 3 hours searching for an answer to the topic, I get - a lazy step. Ocean Market fits all theme criteria, unlike other applications

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
well, the build and most obvious use of c2d is the ocean market, which has been tweeted over 4 years ad nauseum. I understand if you feel this was a good choice, and perhaps my wording was sharp. However, the point of being an ambassador is to educate the public and promote the tech space outside the obvious.
In fact I did not disqualify the threads, but left them in. Ocean market is not the focus on what Ocean can do, and we need to push traction and build outside of what is an obvious fallback, c2d was publicly shipped via the marketplace, but there are limitless builds that can be done with the tech.

Author: himas.
Content: I've only been studying Ocean for about 2-3 months and I can't know what was used 4 years ago until then. The predictoor threads , which we have done several times in a row , fall under the same wording . And nothing terrible happened . The question sounded like this : Write about a dApp that uses Ocean's compute-to-data to create insights out of datasets available and add the use of datatokens to sell insights.           Following from the question, you need to write about 1) an application, 2) that uses compute-to-data technology , 3) create insights out of datasets available , 4) add the use of datatokens to sell insights. Under all these conditions, of all the applications, Ocean Market is exclusively suitable , other applications are not fully suitable, since they do not fulfill one or 2 conditions. Some do not create insights out of datasets available, some do not sell at all. At the same time, you put threads about the ephemeral use of technology ( which does not fit the topic at all ) . The above thread is about an application that perfectly matches the topic . I might as well have just written about some Ocean technologies without reading the topic at all , while not getting the risk of disqualification and accusations of laziness . Your criterion - Ocean Market is not interesting for users, since once upon a time there was a lot of information about it on Twitter - is absolutely unfair. I couldn't even know about it in theory. At the same time, Ocean market is a very useful  product that is worth attention. And judging by the number of likes, views and interactions, this thread was very interesting to my audience, it showed the best performance in the entire history of my activities.

Author: himas.
Content: I’m very upset to receive such a low assessment of my work, despite the fact that even more time was spent than on launching Predictoor.

Author: blockchainlugano
Content:
I'm not giving a low assessment of work, the thread in itself was good. The adjective used was in reference to choice in dapp. That it is Ocean's own seems logical that it would be covered to no end.

I think the wording of the task (Write about a dApp that uses Ocean's compute-to-data to create insights out of datasets available and add the use of datatokens to sell insights) perhaps was not clear enough, my bad, and it should've been creative and hypothetical. For those who could not do so reverting to something else out there that exists would be a logical step. There are many products using Ocean that fall into all the categories, that are using insights via the marketplace or their own. We could go into Dimitra, Datalatte, ones covered by other ambassadors. etc. We are trying to spotlight Ocean tech without being 'Ocean' as they have their own Twitter account and inhouse marketing team that covers what they are doing better than we ever could.

As per the metrics, I agree you had many. And the 3 hour workload to create this goes along with many other ambassadors who spend similar amounts on their thread. But I could not in good faith award the top tweets to ones that cover in essence what compute-to-data is instead of highlighting the workflow outside of the given pipeline.

DM me if you want to discuss further.
